
    A
woman, who has been accused of the murder of her newborn baby, was granted bail
of R1 000 in the Lehurutshe Magistrate's Court in the North West on Monday.The
21-year-old mother from Dinokana Village in Lehurutshe, was arrested on
Saturday for allegedly trying to kill her three-day-old baby boy."It
appears that the woman, [whose] family did not know that she was pregnant,
delivered a baby boy without assistance of any person [and] then threw the
newborn into a pit toilet on Thursday," said Lieutenant Colonel Amanda
